  "instructions": "<p>Hunt more focused for bestiary, but you can do a good experience if you come to do a hunt x2, x3 or x4 at low level.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>To enter here, you need to be level 100 and have completed 10 local task points (or 15 if you don't have <a href=\"https://tibia.fandom.com/wiki/Bigfoot%27s_Burden_Quest/Spoiler#The_True_Challenge_.28Warzones_-_Rank_IV.29\">rank \"IV\" from Bigfoot's Burden Quest</a> üë£).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>It's an alternate spot that's mostly empty, but if the Ravenous Lava Lurker hunt is empty, it's a better option than this one.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The way back here is very simple, just choose the side and walk around the corners of the cave until you complete the way around.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Start by luring a few monsters and testing the box, then lure more as you get more confident.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>It's good to be level 200+ if you want to catch more than 5 monsters at once. The Lava Lurker are much stronger than the Ravenous Lava Lurker, on the other hand, they give 50 charm points, while the Ravenous give only 25.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üõ°Ô∏è <strong>Equipment</strong></p>\n<p>Lava Lurkers are neutral against all elements except FIRE üî•, which they are immune. So you can use any elemental weapon, except FIRE.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Use equipment with fire protection, such as the SUN CATCHER or any other item that provides fire protection.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>If you can, use the two powerful imbuements of life and void (highly recommended below level 150).</p>\n<p>If you feel the need, add at least one fire protection imbuement to help with damage reduction.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>‚öîÔ∏è<strong> Charms</strong></p>\n<p>If you are level 200 or less and want to hunt here more often, it is best to finish the bestiary and put DODGE in the Lava Lurker to avoid taking damage.</p>\n<p>Attack runes are not necessary, as creatures are neutral against all elements and the hunt is pure waste.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>üêó<strong> Bestiary</strong></p>\n<p>To make the Lava Lurker bestiary, you need 2500 of them, and per hour I've managed to make about 400, so in like 6 or 7 hours you can finish this bestiary.</p>",
